# Design system conventions

## Primitives

All shared UI primitives live in `src/components/shell/tooling/design-system/primitives.tsx`.
Do not scatter one-off components across window files — extract reusable pieces to `primitives.tsx`.

Current primitives: ToolAppSurface, ToolSection, FieldLabel, FieldGroup, Stack, Inline,
TypeDisplay, TypeTitle, TypeSubtitle, TypeBody, TypeCaption, PillToggle, SegmentControl,
ActionButton, SwitchToggle, TabBar, Accordion, Tag, StatusDot, SliderField, OptionCard,
SettingRow, TextInput, TextAreaInput, SelectInput, RangeSlider, StatusBadge, PhoneFrame,
HandoffBanner, toDisplayLabel.

## Tokens

CSS variables in `globals.css`:
- Surfaces: `--surface-canvas`, `--surface-panel`, `--surface-card`, `--surface-subtle`, `--surface-border`
- Typography: `--type-step-2xs` through `--type-step-2xl`
- Layout: `--layout-gap-xs/sm/md/lg/xl`, `--layout-surface-pad`, `--layout-section-pad`, `--layout-control-pad-x/y`

Always use token variables, not raw pixel values, for spacing and surface colors.

## Styling conventions

- Tailwind utility classes + CSS variable references (`bg-[var(--surface-card)]`).
- Lucide React for icons. Motion library for animations.
- Translucent/glass aesthetic where appropriate (backdrop-blur, border opacity).
- Type classes: `type-display`, `type-title`, `type-subtitle`, `type-body`, `type-body-sm`, `type-label`, `type-caption`.

## Design System Tool sync

After adding or modifying any primitive in `primitives.tsx`, update
`src/components/shell/windows/tool-design-system-window.tsx` to reflect the change.
